  schema:name "sprout" ;
  schema:description "A sprout is a germinated seed eaten before true leaves develop, typically harvested within three to seven days of soaking. Sprouts are one of the simplest crops in [home gardening](../../../index.md): they require no soil, minimal light, and no equipment beyond a container and clean water." ;
